WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:02.919
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: Are you ready?</i>

00:03.002 --> 00:04.462
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

00:04.546 --> 00:07.549
{\an8}<i>♪ I know you see me</i>
<i>standing here ♪</i>

00:08.967 --> 00:11.720
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good,</i>
<i>my dear? ♪</i>

00:12.971 --> 00:15.682
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good today? ♪</i>

00:15.765 --> 00:17.851
{\an8}<i>♪ Today, today ♪</i>

00:17.934 --> 00:19.018
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

00:21.229 --> 00:24.232
{\an8}<i>♪ I'm just another</i>
<i>kind of girl ♪</i>

00:25.525 --> 00:29.112
{\an8}<i>♪ And you want</i>
<i>to see my world ♪</i>

00:29.195 --> 00:31.990
{\an8}<i>♪ So come and run away ♪</i>

00:32.073 --> 00:34.117
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:34.200 --> 00:36.286
{\an8}<i>♪ If you wanna play ♪</i>

00:36.369 --> 00:38.288
{\an8}<i>♪ Come and play today ♪</i>

00:38.371 --> 00:42.292
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's just get away, yeah ♪</i>

00:42.375 --> 00:45.003
{\an8}<i>♪ I will make you see ♪</i>

00:45.086 --> 00:46.713
{\an8}<i>♪ All of the things ♪</i>

00:46.796 --> 00:48.840
{\an8}<i>♪ That you can be ♪</i>

00:48.923 --> 00:50.800
{\an8}<i>♪ Believe in yourself ♪</i>

00:50.884 --> 00:53.928
{\an8}<i>♪ Come follow me ♪</i>

00:54.012 --> 00:55.472
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:55.555 --> 00:57.724
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

01:00.602 --> 01:03.480
{\an8}[pop music]

01:03.563 --> 01:04.188
{\an8}[honks horn]

01:05.899 --> 01:08.485
{\an8}- Oh, come on.
- You come on.

01:08.568 --> 01:10.945
{\an8}- Like you've ever been
stranded on a deserted island.

01:11.029 --> 01:13.156
{\an8}- Neither have you.
- Uh, well, if I was

01:13.239 --> 01:15.366
{\an8}and I could only have one thing,
I would way rather have

01:15.450 --> 01:16.242
{\an8}a pair of socks than a knife.

01:16.326 --> 01:18.661
{\an8}- Why?
- One, socks will keep

01:18.745 --> 01:20.997
{\an8}your feet warm
so you don't freeze to death,

01:21.080 --> 01:22.707
{\an8}two, you can stick
your hand up a sock

01:22.791 --> 01:25.126
{\an8}and use it as a puppet
to keep yourself company,

01:25.210 --> 01:27.504
{\an8}and, three,
you drop a rock in a sock,

01:27.587 --> 01:30.089
{\an8}and, bam, you got yourself
a swingable weapon.

01:30.173 --> 01:31.382
{\an8}- How is a rock in a sock
a weapon?

01:31.466 --> 01:33.676
{\an8}- Why don't you close your eyes
and I'll show you?

01:33.760 --> 01:35.303
{\an8}- I don't want to close my eyes
and you show me!

01:35.386 --> 01:37.472
{\an8}- Why do you always talk?
No, you are not!

01:37.555 --> 01:39.474
{\an8}- No. I'm not gonna close
my eyes, and you'll show me!

01:39.557 --> 01:41.559
{\an8}- But you always talk.
- I know I'm always gonna talk.

01:41.643 --> 01:42.519
{\an8}- Just listen.
- Why do I have to shut up?

01:42.602 --> 01:43.520
{\an8}- One, two...

01:43.603 --> 01:45.480
{\an8}- Stop it!

01:46.981 --> 01:47.857
- Can't we live in a world
where socks and knives

01:47.941 --> 01:51.194
coexist peacefully?

01:51.277 --> 01:52.529
- Hey, Zoey,
there's a delivery guy out there

01:52.612 --> 01:55.406
looking for you.

01:55.490 --> 01:57.450
- Wait!
Tell him that a rock in a sock

01:57.534 --> 01:58.785
is not a weapon.

01:58.868 --> 02:00.286
- You don't make any sense.
- I'm handsome!

02:00.370 --> 02:02.038
I don't have to make sense,
you know that?

02:02.121 --> 02:03.998
- Let's stop talkin', okay?
I'm always right!

02:04.082 --> 02:05.083
- No, you're not!

02:05.166 --> 02:06.042
- Or a weapon.

02:06.125 --> 02:07.377
- It doesn't matter.

02:07.460 --> 02:08.586
- Hi. You lookin' for me,
Zoey Brooks?

02:08.669 --> 02:10.588
- Yeah. Sign here.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.842
- What am I signing for?

02:13.925 --> 02:15.552
- Ribs.

02:15.635 --> 02:16.344
- Ribs?

02:19.889 --> 02:21.599
- Who sent me ribs?

02:21.683 --> 02:23.893
- Here.

02:23.977 --> 02:25.478
- Would you--

02:25.562 --> 02:27.146
- Sure.

02:27.730 --> 02:29.816
Oh, my god.

02:29.899 --> 02:30.149
- What?

02:32.151 --> 02:33.987
- Your great Uncle Morris
passed away.

02:34.070 --> 02:35.905
- I have a great Uncle Morris?

02:35.989 --> 02:38.199
- Well, had.
- Aw.

02:38.283 --> 02:39.826
- And he left you some ribs.

02:39.909 --> 02:42.120
That's sweet and...

02:42.203 --> 02:43.162
kind of weird.

02:43.246 --> 02:45.248
- Yeah, this is a lot of ribs.

02:45.331 --> 02:47.208
- Uh, you got more than that.

02:55.091 --> 03:01.014
[light music]

03:01.097 --> 03:04.809
- Okay. Write down three drops
of ammonium paraphite.

03:04.893 --> 03:07.228
- What's the point
of making a liquid candle?

03:07.312 --> 03:08.897
- An everlasting liquid candle.

03:08.980 --> 03:09.939
You never have to relight it.

03:10.023 --> 03:12.817
- I wish I was everlasting.

03:14.277 --> 03:15.069
- All right.

03:15.153 --> 03:17.530
Here, you light the candle.

03:17.614 --> 03:19.490
- Okay.

03:19.574 --> 03:21.284
- And I'll videotape the moment

03:21.367 --> 03:22.452
for posterity.

03:22.952 --> 03:25.413
And...go.

03:26.581 --> 03:28.207
Aah!

03:28.291 --> 03:29.208
[fire alarm whooping]

03:29.292 --> 03:32.587
Oh!
[squealing/talking shrilly]

03:32.670 --> 03:34.172
- What?

03:34.255 --> 03:36.633
- Your eyebrows blew off.

03:36.716 --> 03:40.511
- [whimpering]

03:40.595 --> 03:43.640
[music]

03:43.723 --> 03:46.809
♪ ♪

03:46.893 --> 03:48.353
- All right.

03:48.436 --> 03:50.980
You can keep your ribs in there
until Sunday.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.190
- Thank you so much.

03:52.273 --> 03:53.232
- But then
I need the space back.

03:53.316 --> 03:55.485
I got a big shipment
of tater pops

03:55.568 --> 03:56.819
coming in Monday morning.

03:56.903 --> 03:58.279
- Oh, I love tater pops!

03:58.363 --> 04:00.949
They're like French fries
in ball form.

04:01.032 --> 04:02.533
- You're in ball form.

04:02.617 --> 04:05.578
- Look, why do you have to say
the most ridiculous--

04:05.662 --> 04:06.496
[both shouting]

04:06.579 --> 04:08.164
- Hey, hey!
- Cool it!

04:08.247 --> 04:09.832
- Hey, enough!

04:09.916 --> 04:12.210
Okay. I did not suffer
through two years

04:12.293 --> 04:15.880
of cafeteria college for this.

04:15.964 --> 04:16.673
- You see what you do?

04:16.755 --> 04:18.382
You guys upset a lunch lady.

04:18.466 --> 04:20.343
- There's no such thing
as cafeteria college.

04:20.426 --> 04:21.511
- Just stop fighting
for two seconds

04:21.594 --> 04:23.721
and help Zoey figure out
how she's gonna eat

04:23.805 --> 04:25.390
a thousand pounds of ribs
before Monday.

04:25.473 --> 04:28.351
- What do you guys think
about a rib cook-off?

04:28.434 --> 04:30.979
- What do you mean,
like a contest?

04:31.062 --> 04:33.272
- Yeah. Kids form teams,
everybody sets up a booth,

04:33.356 --> 04:34.649
best ribs win.

04:34.732 --> 04:35.650
- I think people
will be into it.

04:35.733 --> 04:38.027
- Probably.
- And the four of us

04:38.111 --> 04:39.612
could be a team.
- I'm in. Cool!

04:39.696 --> 04:42.240
- My dad's got an awesome
baby back rib recipe.

04:42.323 --> 04:43.199
- Ooh, that works,
'cause my grandma makes

04:43.282 --> 04:45.159
this homemade barbeque sauce,

04:45.243 --> 04:47.078
you'd cry it's so good.

04:47.161 --> 04:48.329
- Sweet!

04:50.081 --> 04:51.374
- Yeah.
- Oh, you see?

04:51.457 --> 04:52.709
Now, that's nice.

04:52.792 --> 04:54.043
- What do you mean?
- What's nice?

04:54.127 --> 04:56.337
- Seein' you guys cooperate
and not fight for once.

04:56.421 --> 04:59.507
- Well, ribs do bring people
together.

04:59.590 --> 05:01.009
- The magic of pork.

05:01.092 --> 05:01.759
- [laughs] Amen!
- Amen.

05:01.843 --> 05:04.053
- Amen.

05:04.137 --> 05:04.595
- Yeah.

05:04.679 --> 05:07.306
[music]

05:07.390 --> 05:10.101
- Ow. Ow. Ow!

05:10.184 --> 05:12.270
- Do you want eyebrows or not?

05:12.353 --> 05:14.439
- Yes, please.
- Then hold still

05:14.522 --> 05:16.524
and stop being a baby.

05:18.276 --> 05:20.069
There.

05:20.153 --> 05:21.404
- Dear god.

05:21.487 --> 05:22.989
- Those were the only
fake eyebrows they had

05:23.072 --> 05:25.742
in the drama department.
- I cannot walk around PCA

05:25.825 --> 05:28.870
with two red gerbils
on my face.

05:28.953 --> 05:29.537
- Hey, guys.

05:31.330 --> 05:32.415
Oh, my god!

05:32.498 --> 05:33.583
Mark, you look ridiculous!
- See?

05:33.666 --> 05:36.335
- Would you rather have
no eyebrows at all?

05:36.419 --> 05:37.670
- By tomorrow morning,

05:37.754 --> 05:39.797
he'll have
his own eyebrows back.

05:39.881 --> 05:40.882
- You found them?

05:40.965 --> 05:42.383
- No. I made this.

05:42.467 --> 05:44.510
It's a follicular stimulant.

05:44.594 --> 05:45.344
- A follicu...huh?

05:45.428 --> 05:47.513
- It accelerates hair growth.

05:47.597 --> 05:49.098
You just dab a little
on whatever skin

05:49.182 --> 05:52.477
you wish to become hairy,
and within hours, hair.

05:52.560 --> 05:54.729
- And it works?
- You tell me.

05:56.439 --> 05:58.941
- Oh!
- Oh, my--

05:59.025 --> 06:00.568
- Your pit's all furry.

06:00.651 --> 06:02.195
- Well, I had to test it out,
so last night

06:02.278 --> 06:04.405
I put some of this under my arm,

06:04.489 --> 06:06.616
and now, tuft.

06:06.699 --> 06:08.409
- Oh!
- Stop showing us.

06:08.493 --> 06:10.203
- Well, calm down.
I'll shave it off

06:10.286 --> 06:11.871
before I go to bed tonight.

06:11.954 --> 06:15.208
Now, get those caterpillars
off Mark's face.

06:15.291 --> 06:16.000
- Okay.
- Uh, wait.

06:16.084 --> 06:18.294
Is this gonna hurt?

06:18.377 --> 06:19.712
'Cause I have
a low threshold of...

06:19.796 --> 06:21.923
[ripping]
[screaming] pain!

06:22.006 --> 06:24.050
[echoing]
Pain.

06:24.133 --> 06:28.304
[music]

06:28.387 --> 06:30.723
- Hey, want to play some pool?

06:33.434 --> 06:34.811
Your loss.

06:36.187 --> 06:37.855
- Coco.

06:37.939 --> 06:38.981
- Hey, Coco.

06:39.065 --> 06:41.484
- What?
- Look.

06:41.567 --> 06:42.276
Dean Rivers just signed this.

06:42.360 --> 06:44.987
- Am I fired?
- No.

06:45.071 --> 06:47.073
- It just says we're allowed
to have a rib cook-off

06:47.156 --> 06:48.825
this Saturday in the quad.

06:48.908 --> 06:50.118
- If we get an adult
to supervise.

06:50.201 --> 06:51.369
- Ribs? Can I be the judge?

06:51.452 --> 06:53.663
- Well, yeah,
we were just gonna ask--

06:53.746 --> 06:55.331
- I want to be the judge!
- Okay!

06:55.414 --> 06:55.998
- You can be the judge.

06:56.082 --> 06:58.459
- Yes!
Ha ha!

07:02.922 --> 07:04.173
- Lola, come on, come on.
Let's go.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.175
- I'm comin'.

07:06.259 --> 07:07.552
- Where are you guys going?

07:07.635 --> 07:08.344
- To grab some breakfast
before class.

07:08.427 --> 07:10.388
Want to come?
- Yeah.

07:10.471 --> 07:14.934
Let me just throw on
some clothes.

07:15.017 --> 07:16.144
- Aah! Aah!

07:16.227 --> 07:18.146
- What? What do you--

07:18.229 --> 07:20.022
Aah!
What happened?

07:20.106 --> 07:21.941
- I thought you shaved it off
last night.

07:22.024 --> 07:23.192
- I did.

07:23.276 --> 07:25.444
It must've grown back overnight
while I was...

07:27.113 --> 07:28.239
Mark.

07:28.322 --> 07:32.827
- Aaah!

07:32.910 --> 07:34.078
[music]

07:34.162 --> 07:36.539
[horns honk]

07:41.210 --> 07:42.712
- You know, I like ribs,

07:42.795 --> 07:44.964
but I feel bad
for the poor pigs.

07:45.047 --> 07:47.258
- Oh, they don't have
to hurt the pigs anymore

07:47.341 --> 07:48.467
to get the ribs.

07:48.551 --> 07:49.886
- That's not true.

07:49.969 --> 07:51.220
- Shh!

07:51.304 --> 07:53.598
Now, you just lay the ribs
down there.

07:53.681 --> 07:55.808
- Okay.
- And I'll apply

07:55.892 --> 07:57.894
the Reese family's
world-famous rib rub.

07:57.977 --> 08:00.062
- World famous?

08:00.146 --> 08:02.231
- Yes. World famous.

08:02.315 --> 08:05.610
- So if I'm walkin' down
the street in Bangladesh

08:05.693 --> 08:07.028
and I turn to some Bangladonian
and say,

08:07.111 --> 08:10.072
"Hey, you heard about
the Reese family's rib rub?"

08:10.156 --> 08:11.240
he's gonna say,

08:11.324 --> 08:12.909
[East Indian accent]
"Oh. Well, of course.

08:12.992 --> 08:16.245
That is a world-famous rib rub.
World famous."

08:16.329 --> 08:18.956
- I have to put up with this?

08:19.040 --> 08:19.540
- Just rub the ribs.

08:21.500 --> 08:22.543
- Okay. Step one.

08:22.627 --> 08:27.215
You sprinkle it
all over both sides of the slab

08:27.298 --> 08:29.592
like this,

08:29.675 --> 08:33.596
then just rub it in
really good like this.

08:35.597 --> 08:38.100
And...there.

08:38.183 --> 08:39.769
- Nice.
- Okay.

08:39.852 --> 08:40.311
Now what about the sauce?

08:40.394 --> 08:43.188
- Ha! All right.

08:43.272 --> 08:45.441
Now, we're just gonna take
a little of the sauce

08:45.524 --> 08:46.984
with this brush, you see?

08:47.068 --> 08:51.739
Then we're just gonna spread it
evenly across the slab.

08:51.822 --> 08:52.281
- That's too much.

08:52.365 --> 08:54.450
- Excuse me.

08:54.533 --> 08:56.911
- You just put a little sauce on
before you cook 'em,

08:56.994 --> 08:59.121
and then when they're almost
done, you put more on.

08:59.205 --> 09:01.499
- You're a <i> moron.</i>

09:01.582 --> 09:02.833
- Just tryin' to help.
- I'm doin' it

09:02.917 --> 09:03.751
the way my grandma does it.

09:03.834 --> 09:05.544
- Well, your grandma's wrong.

09:11.050 --> 09:13.344
- Did I tell you
how to rub the ribs?

09:13.427 --> 09:15.471
- No, 'cause I did it right.

09:15.554 --> 09:17.598
- Come on, boys, play nice.

09:17.682 --> 09:19.600
- No, no, no, no. It's cool.

09:19.684 --> 09:21.477
Ha. Ha ha.

09:21.560 --> 09:22.812
He did do it right.

09:22.895 --> 09:24.397
Ha ha.

09:24.480 --> 09:26.274
In fact, let me see if I have

09:26.357 --> 09:29.443
the rib-rubbing technique down.

09:29.527 --> 09:30.778
First, you get some rub,

09:32.989 --> 09:35.533
then you apply it to the ribs.

09:36.742 --> 09:37.326
That's right,
all in the rib cage area.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.829
All in there, like that.

09:39.912 --> 09:41.998
[laughs]

09:42.081 --> 09:43.582
- Okay, maybe this would be
a good time

09:43.666 --> 09:44.750
to take a little break.

09:44.834 --> 09:46.627
- Wait, wait, wait.

09:46.711 --> 09:49.547
Let me see if I understand
how to apply the sauce.

09:49.630 --> 09:51.007
- The sauce?

09:56.762 --> 09:58.431
That how your grandma does it?

09:58.514 --> 10:00.224
- Ha ha. Yeah.

10:00.308 --> 10:02.184
Let me show you
how she takes out the trash.

10:02.268 --> 10:04.186
- Oh! Oh!

10:04.270 --> 10:06.439
[shouting]

10:06.522 --> 10:07.523
- One more time!

10:07.606 --> 10:08.733
My grandma does so--

10:08.816 --> 10:09.400
- Get off of him!

10:09.483 --> 10:10.484
Guys, break it up! Stop!

10:10.568 --> 10:13.195
- Don't talk about my grandma!

10:13.279 --> 10:15.698
- Break! Break!

10:15.781 --> 10:17.867
Okay. Okay. Okay.

10:17.950 --> 10:19.952
- All right, since you two
can't act like grown-ups...

10:20.036 --> 10:21.620
- We're gonna form
two separate teams.

10:21.704 --> 10:24.373
- Michael, you're with me.
- Good!

10:24.457 --> 10:25.750
- Sadly, I got you.
- Good.

10:25.833 --> 10:30.212
Our ribs are gonna make
your ribs taste like...

10:30.296 --> 10:31.380
bad ribs.

10:31.464 --> 10:33.883
- Well, we'll settle this
on the grill.

10:33.966 --> 10:35.593
- Quinn!

10:35.676 --> 10:38.888
[students hooting and talking]

10:38.971 --> 10:40.181
Quinn?

10:41.974 --> 10:43.809
Quinn!

10:46.020 --> 10:50.149
[music]

10:50.232 --> 10:51.317
- Wait.
I thought you guys

10:51.400 --> 10:52.401
and Michael and Logan

10:52.485 --> 10:53.944
were all
on the same rib team.

10:54.028 --> 10:56.739
What happened?
- Well, there was a rubbing.

10:56.822 --> 10:58.699
- There was a saucing.
- Some grandma-bashing.

10:58.783 --> 11:01.577
- And now I'm cooking ribs
with Michael.

11:01.660 --> 11:03.454
- And I'll be ribbin' it up
with Logan.

11:03.537 --> 11:04.914
- Zoey. Zoey!

11:04.997 --> 11:05.706
- Oh, hey, Dean Rivers.

11:05.790 --> 11:07.541
- What's up, Dean-o?

11:07.625 --> 11:08.542
- Too casual.

11:08.626 --> 11:10.961
- Dean Rivers, how are you?

11:11.045 --> 11:12.213
- Very excited.

11:12.296 --> 11:13.589
Guess who's right outside
the building.

11:13.673 --> 11:16.425
- Who?
- Pierre Le Mange.

11:16.509 --> 11:18.761
- From the food channel?
- No way!

11:18.844 --> 11:20.554
- He's like the most famous
chef in the world.

11:20.638 --> 11:21.847
- What's he doing here?

11:21.931 --> 11:23.557
- He wants to judge
your rib cook-off.

11:23.641 --> 11:25.684
- What?
- How did he even know about--

11:25.768 --> 11:27.812
- I was at the gas station,
he pulls up next to me.

11:27.895 --> 11:29.980
I say, "Aren't you
Pierre Le Mange?"

11:30.064 --> 11:31.315
and he says,<i> "Oui, oui."</i>

11:31.399 --> 11:32.608
- Really?
- Yeah.

11:32.692 --> 11:35.486
So we start talking,
I mention the rib cook-off,

11:35.569 --> 11:37.071
and he just offered
to be the judge.

11:37.154 --> 11:38.239
- That's so cool.
- That's the best.

11:38.322 --> 11:40.908
- That's awesome.
- You want to meet him?

11:40.991 --> 11:41.784
- Yeah.
- Sure.

11:41.867 --> 11:43.160
- Totally.
- Wait here.

11:43.244 --> 11:44.203
- You got a celebrity judge.

11:44.286 --> 11:47.456
- Yeah,
and who's gonna tell Coco?

11:47.540 --> 11:49.125
- Who's gonna tell me what?

11:50.167 --> 11:51.210
- Uh, Coco.

11:51.293 --> 11:53.671
Um...

11:53.754 --> 11:56.215
Zoey, why don't you tell Coco
the exciting news?

11:56.298 --> 11:57.133
- Thanks, Chase.

11:57.216 --> 11:58.843
Um...

11:58.926 --> 12:02.138
on a scale of one to 10,
how mad would you be

12:02.221 --> 12:05.474
if you didn't judge
the rib cook-off?

12:05.558 --> 12:06.809
- [shrieks]
What?!

12:06.892 --> 12:08.936
- Students, Pierre Le Mange.

12:09.019 --> 12:11.021
- I can't stand it
when I'm promised something

12:11.105 --> 12:13.232
and then--oh, my god,
you're Pierre Le Mange!

12:13.315 --> 12:14.483
[giggling]

12:14.567 --> 12:16.861
-<i> Bonjour, mademoiselle.</i>

12:16.944 --> 12:17.945
<i>Mes amis.</i>

12:18.028 --> 12:18.988
- I watch you on TV
all the time.

12:19.071 --> 12:20.489
I made
your butternut squash fries.

12:20.573 --> 12:23.033
- And were they delicious?

12:23.117 --> 12:23.701
- Yeah!

12:23.784 --> 12:25.244
- I knew your answer

12:25.327 --> 12:26.287
before you responded.

12:26.370 --> 12:29.165
- I'm Coco.

12:29.248 --> 12:33.794
- Coco, named after my favorite
warm, chocolatey beverage

12:33.878 --> 12:37.089
with the small marshmallows
that float upon the surface.

12:37.173 --> 12:38.549
- [giggling]

12:38.632 --> 12:42.011
- See, we were hoping
you'd be okay if Mr. Le Mange

12:42.094 --> 12:44.722
judged the rib cook-off
and, uh...

12:44.805 --> 12:47.141
- You were the assistant judge.

12:47.224 --> 12:47.933
- Okay!

12:48.017 --> 12:50.478
- Ah, you are a food expert?

12:50.561 --> 12:53.355
- Oh, you bet your sweet bippy.

12:53.439 --> 12:56.150
- I find you all delightful,

12:56.233 --> 12:58.777
and I look forward
to tasting your ribs.

13:02.323 --> 13:04.241
- I am in <i> love</i> with that man.

13:04.325 --> 13:05.951
- Hey, Coco.

13:07.828 --> 13:10.164
you dropped your pillowcase.

13:12.458 --> 13:15.044
- That is my underwear!

13:17.046 --> 13:20.216
- Well, I'm gonna go
boil my hand.

13:20.299 --> 13:23.385
[music]

13:23.469 --> 13:27.264
♪ ♪

13:27.348 --> 13:28.265
- Look at this.

13:28.349 --> 13:30.392
- Look at this!

13:30.476 --> 13:33.145
- Well, what are we
supposed to do?

13:33.229 --> 13:36.232
[music]

13:36.315 --> 13:43.489
♪ ♪

13:43.572 --> 13:48.160
[razors buzzing]

13:58.754 --> 14:01.590
- This is one of
our brand-new dormitories.

14:01.674 --> 14:03.342
Notice the extra wide hallways?

14:03.425 --> 14:04.552
-<i> Fantastique.</i>

14:04.635 --> 14:08.097
I have never seen
a school hallway so wide.

14:08.180 --> 14:09.473
[cell phone ringing]

14:09.557 --> 14:11.225
- Excuse me.

14:11.308 --> 14:14.103
I should take this.
Just give me one second.

14:14.186 --> 14:16.647
- But of course.

14:16.730 --> 14:17.982
- Rivers here.

14:18.065 --> 14:20.734
Sure, what time?

14:26.532 --> 14:27.449
- Hey, Mr. Le Mange.

14:27.533 --> 14:29.952
-<i> Oui?</i>
- I, uh...I hear

14:30.035 --> 14:31.453
you're judging
the rib cook-off.

14:31.537 --> 14:32.454
- Indeed, this is true.

14:32.538 --> 14:34.748
Are you one of
the students competing?

14:34.832 --> 14:35.874
- Yeah, me and my friend--

14:35.958 --> 14:38.502
a tall, skinny kid, weird hair.

14:38.586 --> 14:39.878
- Ah, it is nice to see
a young person

14:39.962 --> 14:41.547
so interested in cooking.

14:41.630 --> 14:44.091
- Interested in winning.

14:46.802 --> 14:49.638
Oh, hey. What's this?

14:52.099 --> 14:52.808
I think you dropped some cash.

14:52.891 --> 14:55.519
- But I don't think--

14:55.603 --> 14:56.562
- Take it.

14:56.645 --> 14:58.689
- Oh.

14:59.982 --> 15:00.774
- And, uh, when you're judgin',

15:00.858 --> 15:02.818
just remember, Logan Reese,

15:02.901 --> 15:07.239
the guy who <i> found</i> your $300.

15:14.496 --> 15:18.709
[razors buzzing]

15:23.505 --> 15:24.840
- There. I'm all fixed.

15:24.923 --> 15:28.218
- Well, I'm not.
I have no eyebrows.

15:28.302 --> 15:29.011
I look like a freak.

15:29.094 --> 15:31.430
- No, you just look more...

15:31.513 --> 15:32.431
aerodynamic.

15:32.514 --> 15:34.767
Now, come on.

15:34.850 --> 15:36.769
Let's go meet Zoey and Lola
for dinner.

15:36.852 --> 15:38.771
- I'm not going out in public
like this.

15:38.854 --> 15:40.147
- [sigh] All right.

15:40.230 --> 15:42.566
I'll bring you something back.
- Thanks.

15:42.650 --> 15:43.859
Can I get a plain potato
and a napkin?

15:43.942 --> 15:47.321
- Sure. No butter, sour cream?

15:48.906 --> 15:51.784
Plain potato and a napkin.

15:59.500 --> 16:00.876
- Oh...

16:00.959 --> 16:03.587
[cracking sound]
Oh! This is helping my back

16:03.671 --> 16:05.047
more than you can understand.

16:05.130 --> 16:06.965
- Oh, that's good to hear.

16:07.049 --> 16:08.759
You just relax and enjoy.

16:08.842 --> 16:10.427
- Very well,
but you must let me pay you

16:10.511 --> 16:11.845
for this massage.

16:11.929 --> 16:13.430
- Now, now,
you just remember me,

16:13.514 --> 16:15.808
Michael Barret,

16:15.891 --> 16:16.934
when you're judging
that rib cook-off.

16:17.017 --> 16:18.268
- Oh. How can I forget?

16:18.352 --> 16:20.396
You have hands
like a lumberjack.

16:20.479 --> 16:21.730
- Oh! You flatter me.

16:21.814 --> 16:22.731
Look out!

16:22.815 --> 16:25.025
Here comes the chop-a-matic.

16:25.109 --> 16:26.568
- Ohhh!

16:26.652 --> 16:28.821
Ohhh! Ohhh!

16:28.904 --> 16:31.407
- Ha ha. You like that.
I know.

16:31.490 --> 16:34.410
[music]

16:34.493 --> 16:38.205
♪ ♪

16:38.288 --> 16:39.456
- Hey, sweety.

16:39.540 --> 16:42.584
I got you the biggest
baked potato I could--

16:42.668 --> 16:43.919
Mark!

16:44.002 --> 16:45.337
- They're back.

16:45.421 --> 16:46.463
- I've only been gone
for an hour.

16:46.547 --> 16:48.173
How could--

16:52.219 --> 16:54.930
Aah!
How could this happen?

16:55.013 --> 16:57.766
- You tell me.
It's your follicular stimulant.

16:57.850 --> 16:59.309
- Yeah, but I never knew
it would regenerate hair

16:59.393 --> 17:01.854
this aggressively.

17:01.937 --> 17:04.522
Oh, we're freaks.

17:04.606 --> 17:06.442
- Yeah.

17:06.525 --> 17:08.026
Can I have my potato?

17:09.486 --> 17:11.864
- Oh.

17:15.492 --> 17:22.165
[music]

17:22.249 --> 17:25.461
<i>- ♪ Grab your things,</i>
<i>get in the car ♪</i>

17:25.544 --> 17:28.297
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:28.380 --> 17:31.592
<i>♪ We'll watch the sun</i>
<i>turn into stars ♪</i>

17:31.675 --> 17:33.969
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:34.052 --> 17:36.638
<i>♪ Spread your arms</i>
<i>in groovy air ♪</i>

17:36.722 --> 17:40.392
<i>♪ It's a perfect day ♪</i>

17:40.476 --> 17:44.313
<i>♪ There's no one</i>
<i>bossin' you around ♪</i>

17:44.396 --> 17:46.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:46.273 --> 17:50.861
<i>♪ So just get lost</i>
<i>until you're found ♪</i>

17:50.944 --> 17:52.154
[music stops]

17:52.237 --> 17:53.238
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:53.322 --> 17:57.493
<i>♪ Spread your arms</i>
<i>in groovy air ♪</i>

17:57.576 --> 17:58.452
<i>♪ It's a perfect day ♪</i>

17:58.535 --> 18:01.455
- [sobbing]

18:01.538 --> 18:05.876
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:05.959 --> 18:08.837
- They are <i> fantastique.</i>

18:08.921 --> 18:11.465
- Oh, yes!

18:11.548 --> 18:21.058
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:21.141 --> 18:23.185
- That's my grandma's
barbecue sauce!

18:23.268 --> 18:25.354
- No talking
while Pierre's chewing!

18:28.273 --> 18:29.858
[music]

18:29.942 --> 18:31.193
- He stopped chewing.

18:31.276 --> 18:33.612
- Well, what do you think,
Mr. Le Mange?

18:33.695 --> 18:37.115
- Your ribs are excellent.

18:38.283 --> 18:40.369
- But not better than 9.6,
right?

18:40.452 --> 18:41.411
- Well...

18:41.495 --> 18:45.999
[sirens wailing]

18:52.714 --> 18:54.758
- Why are the police here?

18:54.842 --> 18:56.134
-<i> Jambon!</i>

18:57.845 --> 18:58.846
- There he is!

18:58.929 --> 19:00.597
[blowing whistle]

19:00.681 --> 19:03.725
- He's running!

19:03.809 --> 19:05.144
Get him!

19:05.227 --> 19:07.229
Don't let him get away!

19:11.024 --> 19:12.526
- Cuff him, fellas.

19:12.609 --> 19:13.610
- What was that about?

19:16.029 --> 19:17.072
- You're under arrest.

19:17.155 --> 19:18.574
Come on.
Let's go.

19:20.534 --> 19:22.911
- Why is Pierre Le Mange
under arrest?

19:22.995 --> 19:25.330
- This guy
is not Pierre Le Mange.

19:25.414 --> 19:27.249
- What?
- He's an impostor.

19:27.332 --> 19:29.293
He goes around the country
pretending he's Mr. Le Mange

19:29.376 --> 19:33.630
so he can get free stuff
and special VIP treatment.

19:33.714 --> 19:34.923
- No way.
- For real?

19:35.007 --> 19:36.008
- Yeah.
We've been chasing this guy

19:36.091 --> 19:38.719
ever since
the Burbank tamale festival.

19:38.802 --> 19:39.720
- Oh, my god.

19:39.803 --> 19:41.972
- Burbank has
a tamale festival?

19:42.055 --> 19:43.640
- Put him in the car.

19:43.724 --> 19:45.517
[police radio chatter]

19:49.646 --> 19:51.481
- Wait! Wait for Coco!

19:51.565 --> 19:53.609
- [on speaker] Step away
from the car!

19:53.692 --> 20:00.324
- [American accent] Uh, you
have sauce all over your face.

20:00.407 --> 20:02.242
[siren wailing]

20:02.326 --> 20:03.285
- Great.

20:03.368 --> 20:04.828
This whole rib cook-off
was for nothing.

20:04.912 --> 20:06.622
- No, it wasn't.
- Yeah.

20:06.705 --> 20:08.206
We had some fun, had some ribs,

20:08.290 --> 20:10.834
got to see some cops
tackle some fake dude.

20:10.918 --> 20:12.502
- Yeah.

20:12.586 --> 20:15.589
Right before he picked
<i>our</i> ribs as number one.

20:15.672 --> 20:17.007
- Your ribs don't even come
close to our ribs.

20:17.090 --> 20:19.217
- You don't know about my ribs!
- I know about your ribs!

20:19.301 --> 20:20.135
- My grandma made my ribs!
- All right!

20:20.218 --> 20:22.512
[both shouting]
All right!

20:22.596 --> 20:23.764
All right!

20:23.847 --> 20:24.973
We're all sick and tired

20:25.057 --> 20:26.934
of you two screaming
at each other.

20:27.017 --> 20:29.019
- So from now on,
no more arguing.

20:29.102 --> 20:30.228
- Seriously.

20:35.484 --> 20:36.860
- They're right, you know.

20:36.944 --> 20:37.903
- Yeah.

20:37.986 --> 20:40.405
- So, uh, let's just--

20:42.699 --> 20:44.493
- Oh.

20:44.576 --> 20:47.579
- Beautiful.
- How sweet.

20:47.663 --> 20:49.122
- All right,
everybody grab some ribs.

20:49.206 --> 20:52.709
You guys crank up the music,
and let's get this dance goin'.

20:52.793 --> 20:54.294
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

20:54.378 --> 20:58.090
<i>- ♪ Looking for you,</i>
<i>looking for me ♪</i>

20:58.173 --> 21:00.509
<i>♪ Looking for somewhere else</i>
<i>to be ♪</i>

21:00.592 --> 21:05.514
<i>♪ Life is better</i>
<i>when you're around ♪</i>

21:05.597 --> 21:08.392
<i>♪ Just take me</i>
<i>out of this town ♪</i>

21:08.475 --> 21:10.811
<i>♪ Small minds</i>
<i>can bring you down ♪</i>

21:10.894 --> 21:16.233
<i>♪ Everything's better</i>
<i>when you're around ♪</i>

21:16.316 --> 21:19.361
<i>♪ Put me in the spotlight ♪</i>

21:19.444 --> 21:20.862
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:20.946 --> 21:21.905
- I understand.

21:21.989 --> 21:23.949
Thanks, Professor.

21:24.032 --> 21:27.369
[music plays in distance]

21:27.452 --> 21:29.997
- Well?

21:30.080 --> 21:31.832
- He said, um,
based on the chemicals

21:31.915 --> 21:33.125
and compounds that I used,

21:33.208 --> 21:34.876
he thinks
the hair accelerator effect

21:34.960 --> 21:37.838
should wear off
in three to four weeks.

21:37.921 --> 21:38.588
- Great.

21:38.672 --> 21:41.049
We gotta hide for a month.

21:41.133 --> 21:44.386
[distant music continues]

21:44.469 --> 21:46.847
[whooping, laughter,
music thumping]

21:46.930 --> 21:48.307
- [sigh]

21:48.390 --> 21:49.850
You know,
this is what's wrong

21:49.933 --> 21:52.394
with being a teenager.

21:52.477 --> 21:54.521
We're all so worried about what
everybody else thinks.

21:54.604 --> 21:57.232
So what if you have
giant shrubberies for eyebrows?

21:57.315 --> 21:58.442
Who cares what people think?

21:58.525 --> 22:01.820
- You're saying I should
go out there like this?

22:01.903 --> 22:05.407
- Why not?

22:05.490 --> 22:06.783
- Okay.

22:06.867 --> 22:07.784
And you're gonna go out

22:07.868 --> 22:09.453
with that wad of fur
under your arm?

22:14.833 --> 22:19.463
<i>- ♪ Dim all the spotlights,</i>
<i>la da da dum ♪</i>

22:19.546 --> 22:22.758
<i>♪ It's been</i>
<i>a permanent midnight ♪</i>

22:22.841 --> 22:25.302
<i>♪ Permanent midnight ♪</i>

22:25.385 --> 22:27.262
<i>♪ Permanent midnight ♪</i>

22:27.346 --> 22:29.431
- Why does Quinn even date him?

22:29.514 --> 22:31.516
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:31.600 --> 22:33.143
- Oh, my grandma's sauce
is amazing.

22:33.226 --> 22:35.395
- I know, dude.
- Your rib rub

22:35.479 --> 22:36.772
is pretty good, too.
- I know, I--

22:36.855 --> 22:38.940
- Hey, either of you guys
want to dance?

22:39.024 --> 22:40.525
- Yeah.
- Sure.

22:47.199 --> 22:49.493
{\an8}[both shouting]
- Stop talkin' about my nana!

22:49.576 --> 22:50.994
{\an8}- I wasn't talkin' about
your grandma!

22:51.078 --> 22:53.705
{\an8}- Oh! Ow! No, you're not!

22:53.789 --> 22:54.956
{\an8}Not one more time!

22:55.040 --> 22:56.666
{\an8}Don't ever talk
about my grandma!

22:56.750 --> 22:58.752
{\an8}- Ow!

